The paper presents a dynamic data structure for the compact representation of binary relations, which involves algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions applications in Web graphs and RDF databases, which suggests categories such as cs.DB (Databases) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the data structure, which could fall under categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
